# Naming — moduli product JustLastOne (JLO)

## Regola

File in **PortalAdmin** dedicati al product repo **JustLastOne** (stack, DB, testScript, Prisma):

| Condizione | Nome file |
| --- | --- |
| `JustLastOne` già nel nome | OK (es. `config_project.JustLastOne.mjs`, `discovery-config.JustLastOne.mjs`) |
| Solo JLO / product, senza `JustLastOne` | Prefisso **`JustLastOne___`** (tre underscore) |

Esempi: `JustLastOne___run-all.mjs`, `JustLastOne___product-prisma.mjs`, `JustLastOne___script_seed-lib.mjs`.

## Dedicati JLO (prefisso obbligatorio)

- **lib/** — prisma, match-fixtures, testScript catalog, test meta/deps, my-project-analysis
- **lib/cruscotto-db/script_seed/** — init DB, seed, lib condivisa
- **runner/** — `run-all`, `cruscotto.process.*`, `cruscotto.runner.stack.*`, `kill-product-stack`

## Non rinominare (generici PortalAdmin)

`dev-manifest.mjs`, `portal-paths.mjs`, `config_project.mjs`, `discovery-config.mjs`, `discovery-services-repo.mjs`, `repo-service-discovery.mjs`, `dashboard-server.mjs`, `cruscotto.process.start.api.portal.mjs`, `serve-api-portal.mjs`, `kill-dev-ports.mjs`, `reporter.mjs` (multi-repo report).

## Nuovo file JLO

1. Nome `JustLastOne___<slug>.mjs` (o `.ps1` / `.sh`)
2. Config progetto in `discovery-config.JustLastOne.mjs` / `config_project.JustLastOne.mjs` se serve overlay
3. Aggiornare `package.json`, `dev-manifest.json`, `portal.config.mjs` se entrypoint

## Backward compat

`lib/repo-service-discovery.mjs` resta re-export; implementazione in `discovery-services-repo.mjs`.

